defaultAs previously highlighted, the regulatory framework is completely inadequate, with no 
defaultmonitoring 
defaultof data on trade or ownership, som
defaulte species of primates not being classified and 
defaultreported 
defaultlow compliance. ADI has identified 
defaultimportant welfare considerations in the lack of regulation in the UK, (8) firstly because the DWAA is primarily designed to protect people and is not concerned with 
defaultanimal welfare and secondly, because standards of welfare cannot be monitored if local authorities do not know of, or are not required to have knowledge of, primates in their constituency. 
defaultCommercial operators 
defaultare required to conform to the standards laid 
defaultdown in the Pet Animals Act 1951. The point at which a person becomes a commercial operator as opposed to someone simply selling the 
defaultoccasional offspring of their pet may be ambiguous. Furthermore, anybody or individual may call themselves a sanctuary and 
defaultthus avoid regulation altogether. 
